<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16612&amp;p=206533#p206533"><![CDATA[
&quot;<a href="http://blog.kevtris.org/blogfiles/Nitty%20Gritty%20Gameboy%20VRAM%20Timing.txt" class="postlink">Nitty Gritty Game Boy Cycle Timing</a>&quot; by Kevin Horton<br /><br />Yes, the Game Boy's PPU pauses at times when clocking pixels into each scanline. It pauses when loading each sprite's pattern, at the start when skipping pixels for fine scroll, and when switching from the main plane to the window plane.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Oct 23, 2017 9:31 am</p><hr />
