<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16612&amp;p=206531#p206531</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16612&amp;p=206531#p206531"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Game Boy LCD Rending Diagram]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=16612&amp;p=206531#p206531"><![CDATA[
The game boy's video output takes a certain number of cycles per line. Depending on whether or not the short pixel buffer going to the display has to be flushed and restarted, the dot clock will be halted until this is complete, which in turn reduces the length of h-blank to compensate. Ultimately the line length is the same, just with gaps in it.<br /><br />This presentation covers your questions thoroughly I hope: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HyzD8pNlpwI">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HyzD8pNlpwI</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5314">mikejmoffitt</a> — Mon Oct 23, 2017 9:18 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
